The company of this program is also run by a Malaysian too!!! ~\n\nVarsity Summer Internship Program (Help Wanted)\n\nThe Varsity Company International in association with various universities works with college students during the summer helping them gain the experience to apply the knowledge, concepts and skills gained in the classroom to an actual work setting. This is an excellent opportunity for college students to ease the transition from college into the real world. \n\nIn over 16 years, Varsity Company International, with its CEO Ramesh Retnam was an international student, has helped over 10,000 students finance their education. More importantly, the extremely challenging summer program is renowned for developing students into leaders and preparing them for life. Varsity Company International's mission statement is: \"To help others achieve success through service-minded leadership.\" \n\nAccepted interns receive over 100 hours of training in valuable areas such as the sales cycle, goal setting, record keeping, product knowledge and self motivation. Varsity International takes what students learn in a classroom about success principles or how to run a business and gives those concepts real-life application over 3 intense months. Those success principles become not just good ideas discussed in class, but rather life-long habits. Students essentially learn to run their own business selling educational books to families in their homes.\n\nThe intention of the program is to master a set of transferable skills that will be valuable in whatever profession a student chooses after graduation: communication skills, self discipline/motivation, confidence, and adaptability to name a few. In addition to incredible resume experience and personal growth, a student their first summer in the program earns, on average, $7,400 profit. Upon satisfactory performance their first summer, a student can spend subsequent summers in the program and even be hired after graduation for a full-time position with Varsity International or one of the other companies within the corporate family. The summer program also fosters entrepreneurial spirit, so that students who have great business ideas are coached on how to best execute them.\n\nStudents who are admitted to the program will be able to build up their resume through challenging work experience, receive training on relationship building, problem solving, work as part of a team and also save some money. Our interns also have the opportunity to run a business in a different part of the country, showing interviewers that they are mature enough to handle relocation - a major selling point in career interviews.\n\nJust recently, we had a couple of students dropped out from our program dropped out last minute. Because of this, not only American soldiers had to evacuate, but any South Vietnamese that wanted to remain out of captivity or even alive had to escape. Many Vietnamese escaped illegally to the Philippines (including my own father and siblings), many died, many captured and many families were separated, either for many years or permanently. \n\nMany Vietnamese of that generation may be bitter about this, and it would make sense. They were banished from their homes and forced to occupy other countries that may or may not seem welcoming. However, we are a new generation of people, and have the golden opportunity to unite the Vietnamese communities together.\n\nFor those who are lucky enough to have family members make it to a better life after seeking refuge, or simply surviving, go and ask them about this day and find out more! I am conducting a study about life \nexperiences of Asian American women. It is my hope that with this study, \nI can contribute to the understanding of the experiences of Asian \nAmerican women. Your participation is essential to achieving this goal, \nso I hope that you will take part in my study.\n\nIn order to participate, you must identify as an Asian American woman, \nreside in the U.S., and be 18 years of age or older. If you would like \nto participate in my study, please click the link below and you will be \ndirected to the online survey.\n\nhttps://www.surveymonkey.com/s/aawexp\n\nThank you VERY much in advance for your time, and please feel free to \npass on this link to other Asian American women whom you think might be \ninterested in participating.\n\nIf you have any question about this study, please contact Yu-Ping Huang \n(e-mail: yhmpc@ufl.edu), doctoral student in the Department of \nPsychology, or project supervisor, Bonnie Moradi, Ph.D. (e-mail: \nmoradib@ufl.edu), Associate Professor in the Department of Psychology, \nUniversity of Florida. This research has been approved by the University \nof Florida Institutional Review Board (UFIRB#2011-U-0526).\n\nSincerely,\n\nYu-Ping Huang", "type": "status", "id": "2200034365_10150271289149366"}
